         <abstract>
            <p>Les corps glorieux des mots et des êtres could be read as an autobiography or/and an essay. It could also be seen as a tentative evaluation of a process or a rereading of the traditions and history of Zaïre and Africa in order to assess historical responsibility and apprehend the present unrest and the social, political, cultural and spiritual contradictions of the continent.</p>
         </abstract>
